text:
Homebrew / Terminal / Shell
All my apps will be installed using Homebrew, the best package manager for Mac. Install it using the terminal and enter the following line:


Code
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"


From now, go to brew.sh to retrieve the commands to install your favorite apps. A list of apps can be saved in a txt file and installed from there.


Code
nano appstoinstall.txt
<paste apps>

xargs brew install < apps.txt


